delete_thru_substrate_insts(25.10)          delete_thru_substrate_insts(25.10)

Name
       delete_thru_substrate_insts  - Deletes thru-substrate instances for the
       specified net

Syntax
       delete_thru_substrate_insts

       [-help]

       {-net <net_name>}

       Deletes thru-substrate instances for the  specified  net.  A  thru-sub-
       strate  instance  is  a  device  that tunnels through a chip to connect
       frontside routing with backside routing.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each delete_thru_substrate_insts parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man delete_thru_substrate_insts

       -net <net_name>
              Specifies the net  whose  thru-substrate  instances  are  to  be
              deleted.

Related Information
       add_thru_substrate_insts

